inlineContent.text: An object that obtains the various API objects your plug-in needs for communicating with the host application.

Using this protocol, your plug-in can render select portions of its output, or tiles, to increase efficiency and to operate outside the host’s process. Your plug-in should saves a weak reference to the
object to use in subsequent calls. The plug-in initializes its properties and instance variables and returns a pointer to
. If any part of initialization fails in an unrecoverable way, this method returns
